all_metrics = {}

def draw_roc_auc(clf, X_test, y_test, modelname = None, acc_score = None):
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, clf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1])
        
    plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = [10,10]

    plt.plot(fpr, tpr)
    plt.plot([0.0, 1.0], [0.0, 1.0], ls='--', color="green")

    plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
    plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
    auc_score = auc(fpr, tpr)
    
    if (modelname and acc_score):
        print("Accuracy of {} model on test data: {}".format(modelname, acc_score))
        
        if (not all_metrics.get(modelname)):
            all_metrics[modelname] = {}

        all_metrics[modelname]['AUC'] = auc_score
        all_metrics[modelname]['ACC'] = acc_score
    
    plt.title("AUC Score: {}".format(auc_score))
    
    plt.show()
    
def draw_feature_importance(feature_importances, columns, modelname):
    matplotlib.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (8.0, 8.0)

    feature_importances = pd.Series(feature_importances.reshape(-1), index=columns)    
    feature_importances = feature_importances.sort_values()
    print(feature_importances)
    feature_importances.plot(kind = "barh")

    plt.title("Feature importance for {} Model".format(modelname))
    plt.show()
    
def classification_metrics_report(X_test, X_train, y_test, y_train, modelname, is_add_all_metrics):
    X_test_predictions = clf.predict(X_test)
    X_train_predictions = clf.predict(X_train)

    target_names = ["negative class", "positive class"]
    test_report = classification_report(
        y_test, 
        X_test_predictions, 
        target_names=target_names, 
        output_dict=True
    )
    train_report = classification_report(
        y_train, 
        X_train_predictions, 
        target_names=target_names, 
        output_dict=True
    )
    if (is_add_all_metrics):
        all_metrics[modelname]['test_p'] = test_report['positive class']
        all_metrics[modelname]['test_n'] = test_report['negative class']
        all_metrics[modelname]['train_p'] = test_report['positive class']
        all_metrics[modelname]['train_n'] = test_report['negative class']

    print("\nTest data:")
    display(pd.DataFrame.from_dict(test_report).T)

    print("\nTrain data:")
    display(pd.DataFrame.from_dict(train_report).T)

df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(all_metrics).T.sort_values(by=['AUC'], ascending=False)

df['test_precision_p'] = df['test_p'].apply(lambda x: x['precision'])
df['test_recall_p'] = df['test_p'].apply(lambda x: x['recall'])
df['test_f1_score_p'] = df['test_p'].apply(lambda x: x['f1-score'])

df['train_precision_p'] = df['train_p'].apply(lambda x: x['precision'])
df['train_recall_p'] = df['train_p'].apply(lambda x: x['recall'])
df['train_f1_score_p'] = df['train_p'].apply(lambda x: x['f1-score'])

df['test_precision_n'] = df['test_n'].apply(lambda x: x['precision'])
df['test_recall_n'] = df['test_n'].apply(lambda x: x['recall'])
df['test_f1_score_n'] = df['test_n'].apply(lambda x: x['f1-score'])

df['train_precision_n'] = df['train_n'].apply(lambda x: x['precision'])
df['train_recall_n'] = df['train_n'].apply(lambda x: x['recall'])
df['train_f1_score_n'] = df['train_n'].apply(lambda x: x['f1-score'])

df.drop(['test_p', 'train_p', 'test_n', 'train_n'], axis=1, inplace=True)

#          
def get_startdate_minus_paydate(x):
    return (x['start_date'].to_pydatetime() - x['pay_date'].to_pydatetime()).days

#          
def get_paydate_minus_regdate(x):
    return (x['pay_date'].to_pydatetime() - x['regdate'].to_pydatetime()).days / 30

#  ,   
def get_weekday(x):
    return x['expiration_date'].to_pydatetime().weekday() / 7

#  /  ,   
def get_month(x):
    return x['expiration_date'].to_pydatetime().month / 4

#  ,   
def get_monthday(x):
    return x['expiration_date'].to_pydatetime().day / 30

# ,   
def get_year(x):
    return x['expiration_date'].to_pydatetime().year

#    -      
def add_num_services(df):
    users = df["user_id"].values
    df["nservices"] = 0
    for u in users:
        _df = df[df["user_id"] == u]
        g = _df.groupby(by=["service_id"])
        service_ids = list(g.groups.keys())
        for n,s in enumerate(service_ids):
            idx = df[(df["user_id"] == u) & (df["service_id"] == s)].index
            df.at[idx, "nservices"] = n + 1
    return df

Чтение данных и добавление новых features¶

In [28]:
#  
#  
df_history = pd.read_csv("history.csv", parse_dates=["pay_date", "start_date", "expiration_date", "on_date"])
#  
df_test = pd.read_csv("test.csv", parse_dates=["on_date"])
#   
df_users = pd.read_csv("users.csv", parse_dates=["regdate"])

#        
def get_features(df):
    df = add_num_services(df)
    df["cumsum_amount"] = df["amount"].cumsum()
    df["regdate"] = df["user_id"].apply(lambda x: df_users[df_users["user_id"] == x]["regdate"].values[0])
    df["start_minus_pay"] = df.apply(get_startdate_minus_paydate, axis=1)
    df["season"] = df.apply(get_month, axis=1)
    df["pay_minus_reg"] = df.apply(get_paydate_minus_regdate, axis=1)
    return df

#   ,   ,  
df_history = df_history\
    .sort_values(["service_id", "pay_date", "start_date"])\
    .groupby("service_id")\
    .apply(get_features)

#       
df_history["test"] = df_history["churn"].isnull()

#  
used_cols = ["nth_renewal", "cumsum_amount", "start_minus_pay", "pay_minus_reg", "season", "nservices"]
#  
target_col = "churn"

#  
X_train = df_history.query("~test")[used_cols]
y_train = df_history.query("~test")[target_col]
#  () 
X_test = df_history.query("test")[used_cols]
y_test = df_test[target_col]

                    warm_start=True,
